dooyit.parser

Class TagParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • dooyit.parser.TagParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParserCommons
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DeleteParser, FloatParser, MarkParser, MoveParser, UnmarkParser, UnmoveParser

    public class TagParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParserCommons
    TagParser class takes in a string of task IDs and returns an array list of task IDs. It is a parent class of DeleteParser, MarkParser, MoveParser, UnmarkParser and UnmoveParser. It implements the ParserCommons interface to use the shared constants.
    Author:
    Annabel

      • isIntervalType

        Check if the current string is a valid interval of taskIDs

        Returns:

      • checkIfStartAndEndAreNumbers

        private static boolean checkIfStartAndEndAreNumbers(java.lang.String[] splitByDash)
        Checks if there is a correct number of elements in the String array. If the number of elements is correct, checks if the start and end strings are valid numbers.
        Parameters:
        splitByDash - String array of one of the words from the user input that contains the interval marker
        Returns:
        true if the number of elements in the String array is correct and also if the words are valid numbers.

      • getSingleMultipleTagType

        protected TagParser.TagType getSingleMultipleTagType()
        Checks if the user input has one task ID or more and returns the correct TagType.
        Returns:
        the SINGLE TagType if the ArrayList only has one element or the MULTIPLE TagType if the ArrayList has more than one element or the INVALID TagType the ArrayList does not contain any elements.
